        Real Estate Agent Disclosure of Interest in Queensland: What Sellers Need to Know
      </h1>
      <p style="font-size:1rem;color:rgba(240,236,228,0.6);line-height:1.8;max-width:54ch;">
        Under Queensland law, a real estate agent must disclose any personal or financial interest they have in a property transaction. Here is what that obligation covers, when it applies, and what sellers should do with the information.
      </p>
